Definition: arouse hostility or indifference in where there had formerly been love, affection, or friendliness
Example: She alienated her friends when she became fanatically religious
Synonyms: noun, state, estrangement, alienate, person, alienator, disaffect, feeling, disaffection, verb, change, arouse, hostility, or, indifference, in, where, there, had, formerly, been, love, affection, friendliness, She, alienated, her, friends, when, she, became, fanatically, religious
Frame: 9,10
Category: verb.emotion
